# FinSense Project Analysis

## 📊 Executive Summary

**FinSense** is an **AI-Powered Wealth Intelligence System** that uses machine learning to automatically categorize transactions, predict future financial outcomes, and provide actionable insights through an intuitive dashboard. The project is marked as **PRODUCTION READY** with a 100% validation pass rate (81/81 checks).

---

## 🎯 Project Concept & Purpose

### What Problem Does It Solve?
FinSense addresses the challenge of manual financial tracking and planning by:
- **Eliminating manual transaction categorization** through ML-powered clustering
- **Predicting financial health** using time-series forecasting (30-day projections)
- **Providing proactive alerts** before overspending occurs
- **Offering real-time insights** through interactive visualizations

### Target Users
- Individuals seeking automated personal finance management
- Users wanting predictive insights into their financial health
- People who want to avoid overspending through intelligent alerts

---

## 🏗️ Architecture Overview

FinSense follows a **microservices architecture** with three main components:

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Client Layer"
        A[React Frontend<br/>TypeScript + Tailwind]
    end
    
    subgraph "API Layer"
        B[Node.js Backend<br/>Express + JWT Auth]
    end
    
    subgraph "ML Layer"
        C[Python ML Service<br/>Flask + TensorFlow]
    end
    
    subgraph "Data Layer"
        D[(MongoDB)]
    end
    
    subgraph "Real-time Communication"
        E[WebSocket Server<br/>Monitoring + Updates]
    end
    
    A <-->|REST API| B
    A <-->|WebSocket| E
    B <-->|REST API| C
    B <-->|Queries| D
    C <-->|Read/Write| D
    E <-->|Broadcast| A
    
    style A fill:#61dafb
    style B fill:#68a063
    style C fill:#3776ab
    style D fill:#47a248
    style E fill:#ff6b6b
```

### Component Responsibilities

| Component | Technology | Port | Primary Responsibilities |
|-----------|-----------|------|-------------------------|
| **Frontend** | React + TypeScript | 3000 | UI/UX, routing, state management, visualizations |
| **Backend** | Node.js + Express | 5000 | API gateway, authentication, business logic, WebSocket |
| **ML Service** | Python + Flask | 5001 | Transaction categorization, predictions, stress scoring |
| **Database** | MongoDB | 27017 | Data persistence, aggregations, indexing |

